{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"rotation","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Vector3","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector3V","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector3"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"set"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the mathematical sense, rotation is a matrix and not a vector. The three Euler angles, which are the three independent parameters of the Euler-angle parametrization of the rotation matrix, are stored in a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector3","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" data structure not because the rotation is a vector, but only because "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector3"},{"type":"text","text":" exists as a convenient data-structure to store 3 floating-point numbers. Therefore, applying affine operations on the rotation “vector” is not meaningful."}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property is edited in the inspector in degrees. If you want to use degrees in a script, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Node3D\/rotationDegrees"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note"}]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Rotation part of the local transformation in radi